Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Resurgent 2019 Gathering in Atlanta, Georgia. He thanked the attendees and expressed his gratitude for their support. Pence highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, such as job creation, tax cuts, and deregulation. He also praised the President's commitment to strong national defense and support for the military. Pence criticized the Democratic Party for advocating for socialism and open borders, stating that these policies would harm the country. He called on conservatives to continue fighting for their principles and to support President Trump's re-election campaign. Pence ended his speech by urging the audience to have faith in the American people and in the future of the conservative movement.